[According to the data on the Worldometer website, the total number of cases of COVID-19 worldwide has now crossed 3 million (3 064 225), with reports of cases by 214 countries and territories worldwide. The total number of confirmed cases reported from outside China now represents 97.3% of the total number of reported cases. The epicenter has shifted outside of China to Western Europe and the USA. The USA, with over 1 million confirmed cases now represents 33.0% of the global cases of COVID-19. A global total of 211 449 deaths have been reported, 206 816 (97.8%) outside mainland China.

In descending rank order, the USA is number 1 for numbers of confirmed cases of COVID-19, Spain is number 2, and Italy is number 3, followed by France, Germany, UK, Turkey, Iran, Russia, and China as number 10, with Russia now having surpassed China in cumulative case counts. - Mod.MPP]

